cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Multipath QUIC Performance Evaluation with Controlled Network Topologies
abstract: The dataset documents a controlled experiment measuring throughput, latency,
  and energy consumption of multipath QUIC implementations across three nodes configured
  as client, proxy, and server. Each run applies token‑bucket bandwidth limits and
  netem delay to emulate fast‑path and slow‑path links, varying scheduler policies
  and congestion control algorithms. Performance metrics are logged per iteration,
  aggregated into structured directories, and visualized with a reproducible Python
  pipeline before secure upload to remote storage for downstream analysis.
